      <h1 class="article-title">The Cloud-Forest Leaves: Vietnam's Ancient Shan Tuyet Tea</h1>
      <p class="article-subtitle">In a mist-soaked realm where limestone pinnacles pierce clouds at 1,800 meters and tea trees older than empires twist through primordial forest, the H'Mông and Dao guardians harvest leaves of impossible complexity — <em>Shan Tuyet</em>, the snow-covered mountain tea.</p>
